We say the return type of "abc" is "void". The type inferencer sees the sdoc comment and does not infer the return statement. Since there is no @return tag in the sdoc comment, the return type becomes "void". In this case, if a function has return statements, we should infer their types, using any @param type hints as appropriate.;8

